WEBVTT

00:01.016 --> 00:02.828
<i>Previously on</i>
"This Is Us"...

00:02.944 --> 00:04.567
Do you want to go on a drive?

00:04.655 --> 00:06.070
Where do you want to go?

00:06.178 --> 00:07.671
Los Angeles.

00:08.316 --> 00:11.340
My mom says I'm nuts for doing
this with a guy I barely know.

00:11.428 --> 00:13.476
We've known each other
a whole week.

00:13.837 --> 00:15.183
So, keep in touch.

00:15.532 --> 00:17.392
Definitely keep us posted
on what you're up to.

00:17.562 --> 00:19.443
<i>He said that I
was "Pittsburgh good",</i>

00:20.021 --> 00:22.509
which I've decided to take
as a compliment.

00:27.204 --> 00:28.792
Let's go home.

00:53.960 --> 00:55.246
Hey.

00:56.033 --> 00:57.038
Hey.

00:57.332 --> 00:58.448
Mm?

00:59.887 --> 01:01.380
We're home.

01:03.034 --> 01:04.430
Oh, wow.

01:07.506 --> 01:08.992
How long have I been out?

01:09.301 --> 01:10.934
..Just a little while.

01:13.312 --> 01:14.783
So...

01:15.792 --> 01:17.294
great third date.

01:17.511 --> 01:18.684
I thought so.

01:21.093 --> 01:22.545
Isn't it crazy?

01:22.688 --> 01:25.000
- Hmm?
- How, just a couple weeks ago,

01:25.088 --> 01:27.481
I was a girl singing at a bar
and...

01:27.854 --> 01:30.001
I locked eyes
with a cute guy...

01:30.334 --> 01:32.039
No. No, no, not you.

01:32.127 --> 01:33.587
There was another guy
there, and then he left.

01:33.674 --> 01:34.947
- Ah.
- And I saw you

01:35.050 --> 01:36.330
and I was like, "He'll do".

01:36.418 --> 01:37.926
Okay, yeah.
No, I got it.

01:40.263 --> 01:42.563
It's so strange,
isn't it?

01:42.996 --> 01:44.231
How, just like that,

01:44.318 --> 01:48.802
a complete stranger can become
such a big part of your story.

02:01.366 --> 02:03.620
<i>It's actually kind of
terrifying, you know?</i>

02:04.838 --> 02:07.086
How a single cross
with one person

02:07.173 --> 02:09.238
you've never met can change...

02:09.326 --> 02:10.893
<i>everything.</i>

02:12.191 --> 02:13.083
Yo.

02:13.171 --> 02:14.632
- What's up?
- Malik. What's up, man?

02:14.783 --> 02:15.982
- What's up, man?
- You good?

02:16.070 --> 02:17.216
- Come on in here. Come on.
- I see you,

02:17.303 --> 02:18.718
- I see you.
- Let's go.

02:19.670 --> 02:21.774
All right,
I'm stalling.

02:21.908 --> 02:25.209
'Cause I don't want to get out
of this car.

02:26.963 --> 02:28.472
Which is odd for me,

02:28.560 --> 02:30.342
'cause it's usually the...

02:30.689 --> 02:33.065
bad-boy musicians I like

02:33.185 --> 02:36.226
when it comes to
life-changing strangers.

02:49.647 --> 02:51.188
Okay.

02:52.415 --> 02:54.905
Uh, just so you know,

02:55.119 --> 02:56.859
I am gonna play it cool here,

02:56.947 --> 02:58.465
so don't expect
to get a phone call

02:58.553 --> 02:59.871
- from me right away.
- Oh, yeah.

02:59.981 --> 03:01.196
Same here.

03:01.284 --> 03:03.119
Yeah, I-I got
a pretty full plate,

03:03.207 --> 03:05.376
to be honest.
I got to find a job,

03:05.463 --> 03:07.045
- couch to crash on, so I...
- Yeah.

03:07.133 --> 03:08.888
I wouldn't expect you
to hear from me

03:08.976 --> 03:10.214
- anytime soon.
- Mm.

03:10.301 --> 03:12.004
Or maybe ever again.

03:12.289 --> 03:14.100
- It's quite possible.
- Yeah.

03:37.070 --> 03:38.584
I'm not calling you first.

03:38.672 --> 03:40.541
I'm not calling you first.

03:45.661 --> 03:47.916
<font color=#FF00FF>*THIS IS US*</font>
<font color=#00FF00>Season 04  Episode 01</font>

03:48.004 --> 03:49.942
<font color=#FF00FF>*THIS IS US*</font>
Episode Title : <font color=#FFFF00>"Strangers"</font>

03:50.178 --> 03:52.336
Captioned by
<font color="#00ffff">Media Access Group at WGBH</font>

03:52.536 --> 03:54.536
<font color="#ffc30f">Sync corrections</font> by <font color=#00FF00>srjanapala</font>

04:10.463 --> 04:11.526
Hello?

04:11.710 --> 04:13.075
I called you first.

04:13.647 --> 04:15.251
<i>Couldn't play it cool,
huh?</i>

04:15.339 --> 04:18.024
No, that's never really been
my thing.

04:19.072 --> 04:21.209
Hey,
can I see you tomorrow?

04:21.298 --> 04:22.601
Yes.

04:23.126 --> 04:25.289
That's... that's never really been

04:25.376 --> 04:26.376
<i>my thing either.</i>

04:27.719 --> 04:29.157
Oh, shoot. Tomorrow.

04:29.245 --> 04:31.160
I'm supposed to have
dinner with my parents

04:31.247 --> 04:32.561
<i>and their friends tomorrow.</i>

04:32.648 --> 04:33.562
<i>They want...</i>

04:33.649 --> 04:34.763
<i>proof of life.</i>

04:35.488 --> 04:37.745
But you could come.

04:38.102 --> 04:39.746
I mean,
it's at their country club,

04:39.834 --> 04:41.437
<i>- so I don't know if you'd want to...</i>
- Yeah.

04:41.524 --> 04:43.872
No, I'll... I'll be there.

04:44.267 --> 04:45.841
<i>- Really?</i>
- Yeah.

04:46.525 --> 04:47.668
Great.

04:48.034 --> 04:49.638
Uh, you do have
to wear a sport coat,

04:49.726 --> 04:51.107
but they have a few there

04:51.195 --> 04:52.714
<i>if you want to just borrow one.</i>

04:52.801 --> 04:55.899
Mm, no.
Nah, I'm... I'm set.

04:56.953 --> 04:58.623
Um, hold on one second.

04:58.711 --> 05:00.705
I'm gonna go find
the address for you.

05:00.793 --> 05:02.072
<i>Okay.</i>

05:18.026 --> 05:19.107
<i>Cass.</i>

05:19.195 --> 05:20.622
- Hey. Hey, guys. <i>
- Cassidy?</i>

05:20.710 --> 05:21.607
Hey. Hey, Matty?

05:21.695 --> 05:23.810
<i>It-It's just me.
Matty couldn't stay up any longer.</i>

05:23.898 --> 05:26.272
<i>He's got school in the morning.
But I pinky swore</i>

05:26.360 --> 05:28.114
<i>I'd ask if you got
his Lightning McQueen.</i>

05:28.209 --> 05:30.991
Yeah, I did. I did.
You can tell him I did.

05:34.241 --> 05:35.487
Sorry I haven't called.

05:35.575 --> 05:36.917
<i>Ah...</i>

05:38.077 --> 05:39.515
Ryan,

05:40.514 --> 05:42.852
I miss you guys like crazy.

05:44.322 --> 05:45.912
First thing I want to do
when this is over

05:45.999 --> 05:47.502
is make breakfast
with you and Matty.

05:47.626 --> 05:48.884
We can have breakfast
for dinner.

05:48.971 --> 05:50.773
Remember when we used
to do that all the time?

05:55.191 --> 05:57.211
I think about that
all the time lately.

05:57.478 --> 05:59.379
You know that, right?
You know that...

05:59.608 --> 06:00.952
..even when
we're not talking,

06:01.040 --> 06:02.617
I think about you both
all the time.

06:02.778 --> 06:04.295
Every minute.
Every day.

06:04.606 --> 06:05.852
<i>I know.</i>

06:05.940 --> 06:07.314
<i>Sharp.</i>

06:09.387 --> 06:11.540
Hey, babe,
I got to go, okay?

06:13.432 --> 06:14.560
<i>Okay.</i>

06:14.648 --> 06:16.108
Okay.

06:17.381 --> 06:18.665
Big kiss.

06:18.866 --> 06:20.099
<i>All right.</i>

06:20.186 --> 06:21.384
<i>Bye.</i>

07:01.359 --> 07:02.424
All right, fine.

07:02.512 --> 07:04.047
It's your waistline.

07:06.576 --> 07:07.690
Oh, Sammy.

07:07.778 --> 07:10.651
Crap. No.
Sammy, get back, get back.

07:11.063 --> 07:12.158
Just stay.

07:34.439 --> 07:35.834
Can I help you?

07:36.554 --> 07:38.075
Sir? Can I help you?

07:38.163 --> 07:39.412
- Oh, my God!
- Oh!

07:39.507 --> 07:40.778
- I'm so sorry.
- Oh, my God, why did you do that?

07:40.865 --> 07:42.213
- Oh, I'm so...
- Why would you touch me?

07:42.300 --> 07:44.348
I'm so sorry. I-I
was just trying to get

07:44.435 --> 07:46.050
your attention. I-I...

07:46.231 --> 07:47.970
O-Oh, my God.

07:48.143 --> 07:49.875
- That scared me.
- I'm totally kidding.

07:50.115 --> 07:51.178
Yeah.

07:51.266 --> 07:52.656
But I'm starving.

07:52.743 --> 07:54.199
So if you could, like,
show me to a table,

07:54.286 --> 07:56.246
that would be really,
really cool.

07:56.619 --> 07:57.961
- Of course.
- Yeah.

07:58.048 --> 07:59.329
- Right this way.
- Can you just...

07:59.416 --> 08:00.474
- Yeah.
- Can you just... Yeah.

08:00.561 --> 08:01.919
Yeah. Thank you.

08:02.921 --> 08:04.000
Bro,

08:04.088 --> 08:05.902
20 minutes is too long
for homeroom.

08:06.019 --> 08:07.958
That's all I'm saying.
It's got no purpose.

08:08.046 --> 08:10.071
- They take roll in homeroom.
- Roll?

08:10.260 --> 08:12.278
Roll?
Hey, Malik, you here?

08:12.366 --> 08:14.178
- Here.
- That took one second.

08:14.266 --> 08:15.640
And we're going into junior year

08:15.728 --> 08:17.279
still losing 20 minutes
to homeroom?

08:17.367 --> 08:18.501
That's all I'm saying.

08:18.589 --> 08:20.591
Oh, that's all you're saying?
Promise?

08:20.796 --> 08:22.996
'Cause you say one more word,
you're giving me a dollar.

08:25.708 --> 08:27.213
That's cool.

08:28.169 --> 08:30.060
- Here, fool.
- <i>Give me that money.</i>

08:30.728 --> 08:32.072
You got it.

08:32.452 --> 08:33.881
Come on, man.
Put the phone down.

08:33.969 --> 08:35.177
You're obsessed with her.

08:35.416 --> 08:37.499
If she was your girl,
you'd be obsessed, too.

08:37.917 --> 08:39.062
All right, guys, look,

08:39.150 --> 08:41.503
last kickback before school
at my place tomorrow.

08:41.590 --> 08:42.764
Malik, you coming?

08:42.852 --> 08:44.258
My mom said we can invite girls,

08:44.346 --> 08:45.824
and I got you on grill duty.

08:46.268 --> 08:47.444
Maybe.

08:47.536 --> 08:49.216
Maybe.
I'll see, I'll see, I'll see.

09:06.457 --> 09:07.862
No promises on the kickback.

09:07.949 --> 09:09.064
But I got to get home.

09:09.151 --> 09:10.298
- All right.
- Told Moms that I'd bring home

09:10.385 --> 09:11.499
some food, so...

09:11.586 --> 09:14.081
- Okay.
- Catch y'all later.

09:19.827 --> 09:20.795
Hey, Ma.

09:20.883 --> 09:23.385
- Got you a burger.
- Mmm.

09:23.564 --> 09:25.283
No, no. Go away.

09:32.291 --> 09:33.650
Mmm.

09:35.160 --> 09:36.374
Not as good as yours, baby,

09:36.462 --> 09:38.292
- but mmm!
- Oh, yeah. I know.

09:39.386 --> 09:41.873
- I'm going to go head upstairs...
- Mm-mm.

09:42.334 --> 09:43.423
Don't wake that baby.

09:43.511 --> 09:45.346
Can't hear you.
Too much food in your mouth.

09:51.695 --> 09:53.196
What you doing up?

09:54.990 --> 09:56.372
Hey, Janelle.

09:56.737 --> 09:58.572
Hey. Hey.

09:59.804 --> 10:02.201
I was watching you
on my phone today.

10:10.736 --> 10:12.818
Hey, look. Look.

10:13.216 --> 10:14.995
That's you.

10:15.082 --> 10:17.164
Aw. Aw, Janelle.

10:17.322 --> 10:18.487
Come here.

10:21.232 --> 10:22.936
Oh, you're getting heavy.

10:23.337 --> 10:25.680
Long way from that NICU, huh?

10:26.300 --> 10:29.276
You know, Grandma said
not to wake you up, but, uh...

10:29.542 --> 10:31.544
Daddy trumps Grandma,
doesn't he?

10:31.794 --> 10:34.383
Doesn't he? Doesn't he?

10:57.180 --> 10:58.853
Can I help you?

11:01.301 --> 11:02.503
Yeah. Um...

11:03.470 --> 11:05.180
I'm looking for a suit.

11:09.868 --> 11:11.519
Can I get you anything else?
Coffee...?

11:11.607 --> 11:13.321
- No. I'm good, thanks.
- Okay.

11:13.409 --> 11:15.475
Wait. Come. Sit.

11:15.855 --> 11:17.573
- Join me.
- Oh, I, um...

11:17.661 --> 11:18.717
Your shift is over, Lucy.

11:18.805 --> 11:20.472
I heard you say that
to the other lady.

11:20.622 --> 11:22.720
Mm. Also heard her
call you Lucy,

11:22.808 --> 11:25.375
just...
so you know I'm not a stalker.

11:25.806 --> 11:27.405
Come sit.

11:31.765 --> 11:33.036
Mmm.

11:33.202 --> 11:35.006
This is amazing bacon here.

11:35.662 --> 11:37.197
This is great for a hangover.

11:37.643 --> 11:39.113
Why are you hungover?

11:39.339 --> 11:40.827
I'm hungover,
'cause, last night,

11:40.915 --> 11:42.330
I was writing a song

11:42.916 --> 11:44.226
and...

11:44.314 --> 11:46.229
I realized
I completely suck

11:46.317 --> 11:48.161
and I'm gonna be
playing cocktail lounges

11:48.249 --> 11:50.156
and country clubs for
the rest of my life.

11:52.135 --> 11:53.492
You're a musician?

11:54.104 --> 11:55.566
I'm trying.

11:57.777 --> 11:59.292
It's bright in here.

12:00.175 --> 12:01.834
- How do you...
- I can see some light.

12:01.922 --> 12:03.590
Just a little.
And, um...

12:04.651 --> 12:07.425
and really, really blurry shapes

12:07.513 --> 12:09.052
but nothing clearly.

12:09.250 --> 12:11.182
- Mm.
- I've been here a few times,

12:11.270 --> 12:12.679
but never for breakfast.

12:12.836 --> 12:14.385
Can you describe it for me?

12:15.019 --> 12:16.125
The restaurant?

12:16.213 --> 12:17.279
Yeah.

12:18.162 --> 12:19.995
Yeah, it's, uh...

12:21.634 --> 12:22.712
..it's one of those diners

12:22.800 --> 12:24.924
that will...
never change.

12:25.716 --> 12:27.423
It's not what I would open.

12:27.550 --> 12:28.608
I'm a chef.

12:28.696 --> 12:31.730
Or... I want to be a chef,
I should say.

12:32.611 --> 12:34.312
But it's...

12:35.230 --> 12:37.039
warm here, you know?
It's...

12:38.040 --> 12:40.542
The food is warm,
the people are warm,

12:40.630 --> 12:42.904
the... room is literally
always warm,

12:42.992 --> 12:44.379
even when it's super cold out.

12:45.006 --> 12:46.189
Yeah.

12:52.052 --> 12:53.341
May I?

12:57.812 --> 12:59.011
Sure.

13:15.363 --> 13:16.682
Damn.

13:20.905 --> 13:23.039
I think
I'll have another cup of coffee.

13:28.396 --> 13:29.871
Okay.

13:32.623 --> 13:33.866
She sleep through the night?

13:34.131 --> 13:36.496
- Not really.
- 'Cause you woke her.

13:36.584 --> 13:38.269
Told you
not to, and you woke her.

13:38.357 --> 13:40.739
- Would you leave him alone, woman?
- "Woman"?

13:41.234 --> 13:43.483
I'm sorry,
you plan on kissing me

13:43.571 --> 13:44.800
with that mouth today?

13:45.030 --> 13:47.296
That is definitely the plan,
yeah.

13:49.103 --> 13:51.593
Grandma and Grandpa
are cheesy as hell.

13:51.688 --> 13:54.208
We've earned our cheese,
thank you kindly.

13:54.296 --> 13:55.956
- Mm-hmm.
- I'm working the night shift

13:56.044 --> 13:57.263
at the hotel tonight,
Malik.

13:57.363 --> 13:58.562
Be home by 5:00.

13:58.650 --> 13:59.748
- 5:00?
- Mm-hmm.

13:59.836 --> 14:02.240
Yes, I know
all about Andre's barbecue.

14:02.640 --> 14:05.338
You're watching the baby.
Welcome to responsibility.

14:05.434 --> 14:07.593
Don't start.
Now, go to work.

14:07.681 --> 14:08.826
Both of you.

14:08.914 --> 14:10.287
Hey.

14:10.606 --> 14:12.402
Promise to shine
that beautiful light of yours

14:12.489 --> 14:14.068
onto the world today?

14:16.905 --> 14:18.709
What about you, husband?

14:20.054 --> 14:21.269
For you?

14:21.658 --> 14:23.580
I'll give it everything I got.

14:26.580 --> 14:28.728
Yeah, cheesy as hell.

14:28.816 --> 14:30.245
Hmm...

14:34.496 --> 14:37.473
You don't need a suit
for a country club.

14:38.313 --> 14:40.772
Navy sports coat is
a much better play.

14:41.185 --> 14:42.646
It'll get you anywhere.

14:42.983 --> 14:44.949
Yeah. Mark my words,

14:45.037 --> 14:46.826
you <i> will</i> be sleeping in this.

14:47.586 --> 14:49.586
Looks good.
Fits you perfect.

14:51.598 --> 14:55.319
You know, I... I just
got back from 'Nam,

14:55.454 --> 14:56.797
and...

14:56.931 --> 14:59.053
haven't quite landed a job yet,
so...

14:59.141 --> 15:01.290
Oh, uh, yeah,
I get it.

15:01.794 --> 15:05.138
Yeah. Somehow my number
didn't get called.

15:05.386 --> 15:06.791
- Really?
- Yeah.

15:07.002 --> 15:09.008
Puerto Rican kid whose
number doesn't get called.

15:09.096 --> 15:10.978
You ever hear of something so crazy?

15:14.543 --> 15:16.269
Look, we're not, uh...

15:17.338 --> 15:20.066
we're not tailoring this thing, right?

15:20.859 --> 15:23.968
So why don't you take it,
tuck the tag up in the sleeve

15:24.056 --> 15:25.856
when you wear it, and
bring it back next week.

15:26.412 --> 15:27.734
Really?

15:28.291 --> 15:30.650
This girl,
she's worth it?

15:31.845 --> 15:34.614
Oh, man,
she's like no one you've ever seen.

16:08.626 --> 16:10.636
- Lasher.
- Roger that.

16:10.724 --> 16:13.073
- Waters. You're with me.
- I got it.

16:13.161 --> 16:14.863
All right, guys, listen up.

16:15.048 --> 16:17.120
Go ahead and set up a cordon
around the building.

16:20.030 --> 16:21.037
<i>As-salaam alaikum.</i>

16:21.125 --> 16:22.724
<i>Wa-alaikum-salaam.</i>

16:24.619 --> 16:26.066
<i>Dalta rasha.</i>

16:39.901 --> 16:41.178
Lasher.

16:41.528 --> 16:42.710
What's up?

16:42.798 --> 16:45.198
- Put a guy at the door.
- Ortiz!

16:45.637 --> 16:46.920
Post up here.

16:47.715 --> 16:49.145
We're losing daylight.

16:49.292 --> 16:50.765
I'm not gonna have my guys
in a row

16:50.862 --> 16:52.502
in the middle of the night
in IED country.

16:52.609 --> 16:54.293
You got five minutes.

16:58.453 --> 17:02.037
Asmaan, you promised me
a photo of Mohammad Nadir.

17:02.125 --> 17:03.351
I haven't received anything.

17:03.439 --> 17:04.932
I haven't even heard from you.

17:05.065 --> 17:07.156
<i>Speaking Arabic...</i>

17:11.195 --> 17:12.232
She says she's nervous.

17:12.319 --> 17:13.195
- People are watching her.
- I know.

17:13.291 --> 17:15.214
- She's scared.
- You need to think about your child.

17:18.294 --> 17:19.915
Tell her to look at me,
not you, when she speaks.

17:23.931 --> 17:25.470
Nadir, the bomb maker,

17:25.599 --> 17:27.258
I need his photo.
The longer we are here,

17:27.346 --> 17:29.156
the more danger
we are all in.

17:36.255 --> 17:38.038
If this dog keeps barking,
I'm gonna shoot it.

17:38.125 --> 17:40.209
You're not gonna do anything
till I tell you to, Marine.

17:40.296 --> 17:41.597
We had a deal.

17:42.695 --> 17:44.506
An immigrant visa and
an expedited process.

17:44.888 --> 17:46.771
If I leave here
without that photo,

17:46.859 --> 17:48.097
you get nothing.

17:50.178 --> 17:51.593
- Sergeant.
- I see 'em.

17:51.681 --> 17:53.095
<i>One Bravo, Echo Main.</i>

17:53.292 --> 17:54.774
Echo Main, this is One Bravo.

17:54.862 --> 17:58.360
<i>Be advised ISR spotted
12 military-age males</i>

17:58.478 --> 18:00.994
<i>moving towards your
location, possibly enemy QRF.</i>

18:01.081 --> 18:02.612
- <i>How copy?</i>
- Asmaan.

18:03.323 --> 18:05.323
<i>Speaking Arabic...</i>

18:06.809 --> 18:08.113
She's asking for water
for the village.

18:08.200 --> 18:10.360
That's more than fair.
I can get water for the village.

18:10.527 --> 18:12.607
All right, Asmaan, I need
you to calm down that baby.

18:13.263 --> 18:15.528
Hey, Sharp! Wrap it up!

18:19.779 --> 18:21.032
Asmaan, there's no more time.

18:21.692 --> 18:22.826
I'm a mother, too.

18:23.469 --> 18:26.227
I have a son...
I would do anything to protect him.

18:26.315 --> 18:27.762
Anything. Just like you.

18:27.977 --> 18:30.406
Your patients here,
they are mothers and they are children.

18:30.811 --> 18:32.393
Nadir is a murderer.

18:32.855 --> 18:34.681
He is hiding amongst you.

18:34.999 --> 18:36.373
You give me that photo,

18:36.461 --> 18:38.810
or the entire village pays,
including you and your child.

18:39.711 --> 18:41.445
Look at me. Stay with me.

18:41.533 --> 18:43.063
Hey, look at me!

18:43.350 --> 18:44.965
Do you think I'm playing?

18:45.480 --> 18:46.928
Do you hear me?

18:47.127 --> 18:48.664
You have five seconds.

18:49.720 --> 18:51.053
Five.

18:51.435 --> 18:52.783
Four.

18:53.165 --> 18:54.579
Three.

18:54.667 --> 18:55.825
Two.

19:01.294 --> 19:02.925
Okay, give it to me.

19:05.713 --> 19:07.328
We'll be in touch
about the visa.

19:07.424 --> 19:09.813
- Water?
- And the water.

19:11.204 --> 19:12.503
Let's go.

19:13.937 --> 19:15.054
All right!

19:15.142 --> 19:16.557
Let's mount up!

19:35.783 --> 19:37.020
Thank you.

19:38.690 --> 19:41.293
- Oh! He's here.
- Oh! He's here.

19:41.381 --> 19:42.403
Hi.

19:42.491 --> 19:44.071
Hey.

19:44.389 --> 19:45.489
Um, I want to,

19:45.577 --> 19:47.635
But there
are eyes everywhere.

19:48.064 --> 19:49.604
- Okay, got it.
- Okay,

19:49.692 --> 19:51.142
so, it's my parents
and their best friends.

19:51.229 --> 19:52.852
My mom is... tough,

19:53.012 --> 19:55.046
I'm not gonna lie,
but my dad

19:55.134 --> 19:57.612
saves all,
and he's gonna absolutely love you.

19:57.785 --> 19:58.870
Okay.

19:58.963 --> 20:00.517
I like your jacket, by the way.

20:00.605 --> 20:01.791
Oh, this old thing?

20:01.879 --> 20:05.026
Oh, and I did tell them,
under no circumstances

20:05.114 --> 20:07.682
are they to bring up
anything about Vietnam, so...

20:08.496 --> 20:09.769
- Thanks.
- Okay.

20:10.189 --> 20:11.357
Everyone...

20:12.119 --> 20:13.852
this is the famous Jack.

20:14.388 --> 20:16.762
Famous or infamous?

20:16.977 --> 20:18.832
Taking my daughter
across the country

20:18.934 --> 20:21.517
just a week after meeting her
seems to land...

20:21.946 --> 20:24.213
squarely
in the infamous territory.

20:24.301 --> 20:26.149
Well, now, honey, he took her

20:26.237 --> 20:28.288
for two weeks,
but he brought her back in one piece,

20:28.376 --> 20:30.124
so he can't be all bad.

20:30.769 --> 20:32.841
Very nice to meet you,
Jack. Sit, sit, please.

20:32.929 --> 20:34.817
- Make yourself at home.
- Thank you.

20:37.316 --> 20:38.830
So...

20:39.282 --> 20:41.953
I heard
you just returned from Vietnam.

20:48.402 --> 20:50.288
It was just
a little fender bender.

20:50.376 --> 20:51.921
I can't... I don't know

20:52.009 --> 20:53.864
- how I'm going to pay.
- Let me see what I can do.

20:53.951 --> 20:55.825
You pay what you can
when you can.

20:55.957 --> 20:57.239
Thank you.

21:00.208 --> 21:01.546
- Hey.
- Yo.

21:01.762 --> 21:04.024
Haven't you seen by the spot
in a minute.

21:04.809 --> 21:05.990
Yeah, I been busy.

21:06.148 --> 21:08.297
Man, you're a Boy Scout now.

21:08.385 --> 21:09.566
It's all good.

21:10.023 --> 21:11.350
The kid has your car in the back.

21:11.438 --> 21:12.938
Custom work's his department.

21:13.750 --> 21:16.346
- All right. Good seeing you.
- You, too.

21:26.652 --> 21:27.747
Yeah?

21:28.025 --> 21:29.336
Sharp?

21:30.891 --> 21:33.095
Nadir came back to the village
a few hours ago.

21:33.498 --> 21:35.453
- Predator drone took him out.
- What?

21:35.949 --> 21:39.077
I-I... thought the point
was ID him, take him quietly.

21:39.165 --> 21:40.745
He's just gonna be replaced
in a week.

21:40.833 --> 21:43.875
Yeah. Well, headquarters seems
to like to play Whac-A-Mole.

21:44.785 --> 21:46.394
How many civilian deaths?

21:46.482 --> 21:48.420
Eight dead,
12 or more so wounded.

21:48.515 --> 21:50.230
Strike caught
the back side of a building.

21:50.351 --> 21:52.234
We think bags of fertilizer
were inside,

21:52.322 --> 21:54.737
because the blast radius
wasn't supposed to be so big.

21:54.998 --> 21:56.446
Your asset survived.

21:56.597 --> 21:58.710
We're working on a visa
for her and her kid.

22:00.620 --> 22:01.953
Gunny.

22:03.091 --> 22:05.325
I promised her water
for the village.

22:06.310 --> 22:07.989
There's no more village, Sharp.

22:21.286 --> 22:23.047
Hey, buddy.

