<i>♪ To you ♪</i>

24:38.185 --> 24:41.320
<i>♪ I told the story ♪</i>

24:41.407 --> 24:44.942
<i>♪ Before I knew the ending ♪</i>

24:46.244 --> 24:48.662
<i>♪ I got an answer ♪</i>

24:49.029 --> 24:51.837
<i>♪ Before I heard the question ♪</i>

24:54.095 --> 24:56.026
♪ <i>How could a stranger ♪</i>

24:56.114 --> 24:59.854
<i>♪ Ever end up being you? ♪</i>

25:01.226 --> 25:02.693
<i>♪ And oh ♪</i>

25:04.617 --> 25:05.974
<i>♪ In the quiet way... ♪</i>

25:06.062 --> 25:08.302
Sam wants to ask you something.

25:08.868 --> 25:11.049
Oh, wait.
Sorry. No.

25:11.198 --> 25:12.713
<i>I</i> want to ask you something.

25:12.886 --> 25:17.723
<i>♪ Enough to get you memorized ♪</i>

25:18.050 --> 25:21.700
<i>♪ I found my way, I found my way ♪</i>

25:21.788 --> 25:23.147
<i>♪ To you ♪</i>

25:25.597 --> 25:26.998
<i>♪ Found my way ♪</i>

25:27.086 --> 25:29.608
<i>♪ I found my way ♪</i>

25:29.843 --> 25:31.448
<i>♪ To you. ♪</i>

25:35.301 --> 25:37.986
Well, I will bet you
anything that South Vietnam,

25:38.074 --> 25:39.908
Laos and Cambodia will all fall

25:39.996 --> 25:42.143
to the communists just
like Ike said they would.

25:42.231 --> 25:45.213
I don't recall hearing any
congressional declaration.

25:45.579 --> 25:47.057
Wasn't even a real war.

25:47.236 --> 25:49.413
- Honey? Stop.
- Well...

25:49.501 --> 25:50.854
Enough. Enough war.

25:51.028 --> 25:52.246
- Uh...
- Yuck.

25:52.334 --> 25:53.819
Happier topics.

25:54.853 --> 25:56.979
So, Jack, it must be nice for you

25:57.067 --> 25:59.616
to just take off cross-country
at a moment's notice.

25:59.703 --> 26:02.282
You must come from a wealthy family

26:02.370 --> 26:04.385
to fund all that wanderlust.

26:05.435 --> 26:07.257
What do your parents do?

26:07.858 --> 26:09.431
Um...

26:12.126 --> 26:13.997
I'm sorry.
Was that inappropriate?

26:14.168 --> 26:16.656
Jack, looks like you
took a little fire there.

26:20.794 --> 26:23.445
Um, I should probably go clean this up.

26:23.533 --> 26:25.543
Mm. The restroom is to the left.

26:25.631 --> 26:28.011
- Do you need me to come show...?
- No, no, no, no. I'm-I'm okay.

26:28.099 --> 26:29.566
Excuse me.

26:33.854 --> 26:36.455
Dad?
What the hell?

26:39.153 --> 26:40.748
It's good work, kid.

26:43.372 --> 26:44.685
Damn good.

26:44.773 --> 26:46.451
Thank you.

26:52.332 --> 26:55.104
Um, M-Mr. Castillo,
look, I-I know you, um...

26:55.343 --> 26:58.374
I know you have a business
of your own, right, and, uh,

26:58.471 --> 27:00.219
- look, if you ever need anything...
- Whoa.

27:01.729 --> 27:03.559
You're Darnell's kid.

27:03.670 --> 27:06.130
And Darnell's kid
and my business are not a fit.

27:10.526 --> 27:12.010
Hey, look.

27:12.401 --> 27:16.351
Yeah, yeah, I'm... I'm
Darnell's kid, but, uh...

27:16.697 --> 27:18.310
man, um...

27:18.960 --> 27:22.062
I'm-I'm also raising a
kid of my own, and, um...

27:24.659 --> 27:25.935
...she's special.

27:26.462 --> 27:29.270
I-I've been looking up
the best schools.

27:29.473 --> 27:31.373
And it's like ten K,

27:31.563 --> 27:33.199
ten K for pre-K.

27:33.620 --> 27:36.412
I mean, my-my parents
do fine, but, come on.

27:36.499 --> 27:38.896
Even you know
they don't do that fine.

27:39.893 --> 27:41.620
I need to earn real money

27:42.771 --> 27:44.282
for her.

27:49.478 --> 27:51.076
I got your number.

27:51.683 --> 27:53.817
I'll call you
when you can grow a mustache.

28:14.904 --> 28:16.588
Breathe.

28:18.096 --> 28:19.692
Breathe, Jack.

28:22.568 --> 28:24.291
- Oh, so many...
- Didn't you work here once?

28:24.378 --> 28:25.460
I did.

28:25.593 --> 28:27.207
Sorry. Sorry about that.

28:27.359 --> 28:29.230
- Okay?
- Yeah.

28:29.695 --> 28:31.706
To be honest,
I've never had lobster.

28:31.841 --> 28:33.487
- Oh.
- Kind of got the best of me.

28:37.318 --> 28:39.754
My parents don't do much, ma'am,

28:39.850 --> 28:41.549
in answer to your question.

28:43.164 --> 28:44.188
I mean, my dad...

28:44.276 --> 28:46.458
he-he's in door-to-door sales,

28:46.546 --> 28:50.375
but mostly
what my folks do is fight.

28:51.958 --> 28:53.520
He hits, she cries.

28:53.607 --> 28:56.096
That's... that's what they do.

28:56.936 --> 28:58.851
I had, uh...

28:59.267 --> 29:00.498
a little brother.

29:01.356 --> 29:02.547
Um...

29:03.739 --> 29:05.583
Basically raised him myself.

29:06.784 --> 29:08.265
When he was l-little,

29:09.301 --> 29:11.905
he had this two-year phase

29:12.138 --> 29:14.437
where he was convinced

29:14.524 --> 29:16.591
there was a monster
living in his closet.

29:18.769 --> 29:21.318
I couldn't convince him
that there was no monster,

29:21.421 --> 29:24.337
so instead, I would sit in
front of his closet door,

29:24.504 --> 29:26.705
and I'd tell the monster stories.

29:28.472 --> 29:30.524
I'd tell it bedtime stories

29:30.943 --> 29:33.293
until Nicky was convinced

29:33.400 --> 29:36.109
that the monster had gone to sleep,

29:36.530 --> 29:38.564
and it wasn't gonna
bother him anymore.

29:39.208 --> 29:40.651
Yeah.

29:42.457 --> 29:43.936
Of course, the monster wasn't real,

29:44.023 --> 29:46.819
but my brother's fear...

29:48.227 --> 29:49.679
that was real.

29:51.897 --> 29:54.597
The sweat on his forehead
was real.

29:56.950 --> 29:59.117
My brother's experience was real.

30:02.535 --> 30:04.535
I lost my brother in Vietnam.

30:09.606 --> 30:11.229
People died.

30:11.630 --> 30:12.973
People that I loved.

30:13.500 --> 30:15.933
So, due respect,

30:16.295 --> 30:19.803
it may not seem like
a real war back here,

30:19.890 --> 30:22.906
but I promise you,
that war was very real

30:23.190 --> 30:25.061
for those of us
who were there.

30:33.331 --> 30:34.418
I know...

30:36.135 --> 30:38.550
a stranger taking your daughter
cross-country

30:38.638 --> 30:41.093
might not have been
your favorite thing.

30:41.996 --> 30:45.129
And I'm sorry that was your
first impression of me, but...

30:45.381 --> 30:46.707
don't worry.

30:47.135 --> 30:48.653
You'll get to know me.

30:49.320 --> 30:50.862
I'm not going anywhere.

30:56.511 --> 30:58.370
Oh, I got to say,

30:59.268 --> 31:01.422
I think
I might be a lobster guy, Bec.

31:35.896 --> 31:36.959
Hey.

31:37.047 --> 31:38.110
Hey.

31:42.545 --> 31:43.770
Been drinking?

31:44.541 --> 31:47.875
I needed a few after another day
of looking for jobs.

31:47.963 --> 31:49.657
Needed more than a few,
actually.

31:51.642 --> 31:52.898
Well, hey,

31:53.685 --> 31:55.248
at least you're finally out, huh?

31:55.336 --> 31:56.449
Yay for me.

32:02.134 --> 32:03.849
Did you drive home drunk?

32:05.004 --> 32:06.559
I don't need a lecture.

32:07.994 --> 32:10.304
Well, hey,
don't have one prepared.

32:12.801 --> 32:15.216
Somehow I missed the last
credit card statement.

32:15.303 --> 32:16.899
We're gonna have to pay a late fee.

32:17.190 --> 32:19.712
Well, that's because you keep
piling the mail on the counter

32:19.800 --> 32:21.500
even though
I keep telling you not to.

32:24.995 --> 32:26.886
I'm doing the best
I can here, Cass.

32:26.974 --> 32:30.098
I'm-I'm... I'm taking
care of everything,

32:30.185 --> 32:32.829
I'm practically
raising Matty alone.

32:32.948 --> 32:34.989
Must be nice to have it so easy.

32:35.152 --> 32:36.937
- Do you have any idea...?
- No, no. I don't.

32:37.024 --> 32:38.652
I don't because
you won't talk to me.

32:38.740 --> 32:41.559
Mom? Mom, come here!
I made a car out of Legos!

32:41.647 --> 32:43.763
Matty, give me a second.
Mommy just got home.

32:43.851 --> 32:46.466
Oh, and the, uh...
the hot water heater broke again.

32:46.553 --> 32:47.962
- Again?
- Mom, come on!

32:48.051 --> 32:49.427
- Come on, Mom!
- Matty, please, come on.

32:49.514 --> 32:52.261
I asked about getting it replaced,
but it's expensive.

32:52.349 --> 32:53.827
It's 12 hundred bucks.

32:54.081 --> 32:55.244
Can you believe that?

32:55.332 --> 32:56.909
$1,200 for a water heater?

33:02.249 --> 33:04.242
Mom? Mom?!

33:06.578 --> 33:10.013
Mommy? Mommy? Mom! Mom.

33:14.140 --> 33:16.104
- Mom?
- Stop!

33:18.913 --> 33:20.580
Sor...

33:21.301 --> 33:22.778
Matty.

33:23.849 --> 33:26.863
- Matty, I'm so sorry. I...
- Um... no, no.

33:27.449 --> 33:28.861
Get out.

33:28.982 --> 33:31.628
- I didn't... I didn't...
- Just get out of this house.

33:45.707 --> 33:47.690
I'm gonna go to the restroom,
I'll be right back.

33:47.778 --> 33:49.248
- I'll get the coats.
- Okay.

33:50.496 --> 33:51.943
Young man,

33:52.411 --> 33:56.011
you know, you walked in here
tonight a bit of an underdog,

33:56.082 --> 33:57.529
to put it mildly.

33:57.712 --> 33:59.476
But you had yourself quite
an evening.

33:59.587 --> 34:02.009
You made a bunch of fans.

34:02.097 --> 34:04.910
Thank you, sir.
Just need the one.

34:04.998 --> 34:06.285
Ah.

34:06.960 --> 34:09.422
You know,
first year of her life,

34:09.629 --> 34:13.188
she only stopped crying
if I held her.

34:13.498 --> 34:15.317
Not her mother, not her sister.

34:15.929 --> 34:17.105
Just me.

34:17.597 --> 34:21.101
And everyone would say
"Oh, she's a Daddy's girl."

34:21.188 --> 34:22.658
And I said, "No.

34:23.175 --> 34:25.630
She is her daddy's world."

34:26.146 --> 34:28.156
Oh, and she still is.

34:30.103 --> 34:31.429
You're a good man, Jack.

34:31.676 --> 34:32.909
I can see that.

34:33.782 --> 34:37.505
I can also see a man who
is carrying things with him.

34:38.295 --> 34:39.366
And I can see a man

34:39.454 --> 34:43.322
who is far more haunted
than he wants to let on.

34:44.731 --> 34:45.818
I don't follow.

34:45.906 --> 34:49.362
I want more for her
than you can offer, Jack.

34:49.813 --> 34:53.230
I will do everything I can
to stop this.

34:53.478 --> 34:55.824
And make no mistake
about this, son.

34:56.503 --> 35:00.316
I'm a lot harder to beat than
an imaginary monster in a closet.

35:02.174 --> 35:04.837
Oh, goodness,
I barely ate, I was so nervous.

35:04.925 --> 35:06.783
- Daddy, thank you.
- Oh, you're welcome.

35:06.871 --> 35:07.792
- Yeah.
- Oh, thank you for dinner.

35:07.879 --> 35:08.911
I love you to death,

35:08.999 --> 35:11.032
but Jack, can you take me
to go get a burger, please?

35:11.119 --> 35:12.686
- Absolutely.
- Okay. Good night, Dad.

35:12.774 --> 35:14.009
Good night.

35:16.551 --> 35:19.538
<i>♪ You were waiting outside ♪</i>

35:19.626 --> 35:23.696
<i>♪ For me, in the sun ♪</i>

35:24.312 --> 35:28.326
<i>♪ Laying down to soak it all in ♪</i>

35:28.734 --> 35:30.140
<i>♪ Before we had to run... ♪</i>

35:30.238 --> 35:32.139
Thanks for coming tonight.

35:32.798 --> 35:35.452
I-I know how boring
this is for you, but...

35:35.666 --> 35:37.739
No, of course.

35:41.767 --> 35:45.534
Sorry. I'm just...
tired.

35:46.399 --> 35:47.773
Well, yeah. I mean...

35:49.230 --> 35:50.730
we knew getting
the restaurant off the ground

35:50.817 --> 35:52.981
would be the hardest part, but
now that it's up and running...

35:53.068 --> 35:54.216
I'm pregnant.

35:54.554 --> 35:56.658
<i>♪ Oh, the glory of... ♪</i>

35:57.021 --> 35:58.899
I'm-I'm sorry. My brain just
short-circuited.

35:58.987 --> 36:00.184
- Did...?
- I'm six weeks pregnant.

36:00.271 --> 36:02.585
<i>♪ Was lost on me ♪</i>

36:02.758 --> 36:05.357
- <i>♪ Till I saw how hard... ♪</i>
- Oh, my God.

36:05.445 --> 36:07.184
<i>♪ It'd be to reach you... ♪</i>

36:07.836 --> 36:09.123
Lucy.

36:09.957 --> 36:11.500
Lucy, oh, my God.

36:12.387 --> 36:14.302
<i>♪ Light-years away... ♪</i>

36:14.462 --> 36:16.934
I wanted to get my career sorted
before...

36:18.188 --> 36:19.927
How the hell is this gonna work?

36:20.015 --> 36:21.825
<i>♪ Light-years away... ♪</i>

36:21.913 --> 36:23.541
Look at me.

36:25.269 --> 36:26.832
Are you looking at me?
I'm blind.

36:28.334 --> 36:29.630
I'm looking at you.

36:29.734 --> 36:33.068
<i>♪ In the shadows alone ♪</i>

36:33.181 --> 36:39.018
<i>♪ You could've been right
