39:53.886 --> 39:54.933
<i>So...</i>

39:55.021 --> 39:57.116
the drinking's become a thing.

39:57.203 --> 39:58.969
It started a few years ago.

39:59.462 --> 40:02.439
It's only gotten worse
since I've been out of the Corps.

40:04.809 --> 40:06.549
My husband and I are...

40:07.042 --> 40:08.957
separated, I guess.

40:09.648 --> 40:11.749
My life's at a standstill.

40:12.610 --> 40:15.226
Actually, that's a lie.
It's...

40:15.805 --> 40:17.195
moving in reverse.

40:17.490 --> 40:20.206
I went from working
in classified settings

40:20.294 --> 40:21.875
to driving around
college students

40:21.963 --> 40:23.598
on a Saturday night for Uber.

40:23.749 --> 40:25.936
No offense to Uber drivers.

40:29.328 --> 40:30.715
I...

40:30.845 --> 40:34.269
I can't... feel anything.

40:34.805 --> 40:37.221
I can't feel sadness.

40:37.309 --> 40:39.390
I certainly can't feel joy.

40:39.924 --> 40:42.141
And I hate throwing
around the term PTSD,

40:42.229 --> 40:43.351
and I know you guys
will probably tell me

40:43.438 --> 40:45.305
that that's what this is,
but...

40:46.261 --> 40:47.735
But when I hit him...

40:54.767 --> 40:56.420
When I hit my son,

40:57.495 --> 41:01.941
I can't
blame PTSD or alcohol or Uber.

41:05.102 --> 41:07.700
It was the cost
of a water heater.

41:09.922 --> 41:11.461
Just brought me right back.

41:11.618 --> 41:12.815
On behalf of the U.S. government,

41:12.902 --> 41:14.726
we'd like to present to you
these condolence payments

41:14.813 --> 41:16.710
for every civilian that
was killed yesterday.

41:17.220 --> 41:19.616
$1,200 U.S. per person.

41:31.425 --> 41:33.419
<i>You guys
know we do that, right?</i>

41:33.776 --> 41:35.270
Dead civilian.

41:35.531 --> 41:36.859
Dead kids.

41:37.932 --> 41:39.594
$1,200 per person.

41:39.682 --> 41:42.384
That's the price of a
life over there. That's...

41:42.730 --> 41:44.962
a price of a water heater.

41:45.721 --> 41:47.636
So when I think about that...

